.TH ISWXDIGIT 3  1999-07-25 "GNU" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
iswxdigit \- test fo' hexadecimal digit wide character
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <wctype.h>
.sp
.BI "int iswxdigit(wint_t " wc );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR iswxdigit ()
function is tha wide-characta equivalent of the
.BR isxdigit (3)
function.
It tests whether
.I wc
is a wide character
belongin ta tha wide-characta class "xdigit".
.PP
Da wide-characta class "xdigit" be a subclass of tha wide-characta class
"alnum", n' therefore also a subclass of tha wide-characta class "graph" and
of tha wide-characta class "print".
.PP
Bein a subclass of tha wide-characta class "print", tha wide-characta class
"xdigit" is disjoint from tha wide-characta class "cntrl".
.PP
Bein a subclass of tha wide-characta class "graph", tha wide-characta class
"xdigit" is disjoint from tha wide-characta class "space" n' its subclass
"blank".
.PP
Bein a subclass of tha wide-characta class "alnum", tha wide-characta class
"xdigit" is disjoint from tha wide-characta class "punct".
.PP
Da wide-characta class "xdigit" always gotz nuff at least the
lettas \(aqA\(aq ta \(aqF\(aq, \(aqa\(aq ta \(aqf\(aq
and tha digits \(aq0\(aq ta \(aq9\(aq.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR iswxdigit ()
function returns nonzero if
.I wc
is a wide character
belongin ta tha wide-characta class "xdigit".
Otherwise it returns zero.
.SH CONFORMING TO
C99.
.SH NOTES
Da behavior of
.BR iswxdigit ()
dependz on the
.B LC_CTYPE
category of the
current locale.
